com.cisco.mscviewer.graph

Class Graph

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cisco.mscviewer.graph.Graph

  • public class Graph
extends java.lang.Object

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      Graph(MSCDataModel dm)
      creates a graph where: Each node represents a sequence of events with same timestamp and entity there is an edge between each pair of consecutive (by timestamp) nodes for the same entity there is an edge between each pair of consecutive (by timestamp) nodes not belonging to the same entity and with different timestamp note: this code assumes that all events belonging to the same entity and with the same timestamp are going to appear contiguously in the global array of events in the datamodel.

      • Graph

        public Graph(MSCDataModel dm)
        creates a graph where:
        • Each node represents a sequence of events with same timestamp and entity
        • there is an edge between each pair of consecutive (by timestamp) nodes for the same entity
        • there is an edge between each pair of consecutive (by timestamp) nodes not belonging to the same entity and with different timestamp
        note: this code assumes that all events belonging to the same entity and with the same timestamp are going to appear contiguously in the global array of events in the datamodel.
